gy of AR 11029 on 27 October when the flaring rate peaked is\nsufficient to power M-class or X-class flares, and hence the modeling does not\nappear to support the hypothesis that the absence of large flares is due to the\nregion having limited energy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Oct 2011 01:09:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-28"}
